cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep neural network approach for predicting defects in microelectronics manufacturing processes based on 3D measurements. This involves modeling geometric variations in manufacturing parameters and predicting upcoming events related to sub-optimal performance. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV) since the paper deals with 3D measurements and modeling. The paper also involves the use of deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper applies the proposed framework to a microelectronics use-case, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
